<p>I want to understand typeglobs better and write small programm:</p>  <pre><code>use Symbol;  open F, '&gt;', \my $var; t( F ); t( \F ); t( *F ); t( \*F ); sub t {    my $fh =  shift;    print "&gt;&gt;$fh&lt;&lt;" . ref( $fh ) ."\n"; } </code></pre>  <p>The output is:</p>  <pre><code>&gt;&gt;F&lt;&lt; &gt;&gt;SCALAR(0x1e67fc8)&lt;&lt;SCALAR &gt;&gt;*main::F&lt;&lt; &gt;&gt;GLOB(0x1e53150)&lt;&lt;GLOB </code></pre>  <p>Why <em>GLOB</em> is returned only in last case?</p>